Accurately Calculate Derived Prices with Pricing Contributors

Use discovery elements to retrieve contributing pricing factors from appropriate lookup tables to accurately access pricing data and calculate a product's derived price. This pricing data is written into a context definition by using custom context nodes. Create a discovery procedure and set the usage type as Pricing Discovery to locate the pricing data stored in the context definition.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions where Revenue Lifecycle Management is enabled.

How: From the App Launcher, search for and create a discovery procedure with Pricing Discovery as the usage type. The discovery procedure uses three pricing elements to help locate pricing data to calculate the derived price.
title: Accurately Calculating Derived Prices with Pricing Contributors
